iggsField.Potential.isBounded_iff_of_𝓵_zero\"><span class=\"name\">StandardModel</span>.<span class=\"name\">HiggsField</span>.<span class=\"name\">Potential</span>.<span class=\"name\">isBounded_iff_of_𝓵_zero</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./PhysLean/Meta/Informal/Basic.html#InformalLemma\">InformalLemma</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"When there is no quartic coupling, the potential is bounded iff the mass squared is\nnon-positive, i.e., for `P : Potential` then `P.IsBounded` iff `P.μ2 ≤ 0`. That is to say\n`- P.μ2 * ‖φ‖_H^2 x` is bounded below iff `P.μ2 ≤ 0`. ","docLink":"./PhysLean/Particles/StandardModel/HiggsBoson/Potential.html#StandardModel.HiggsField.Potential.isBounded_iff_of_𝓵_zero","kind":"def","line":365,"name":"StandardModel.HiggsField.Potential.isBounded_iff_of_𝓵_zero","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L365-L370"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/Particles/StandardModel/HiggsBoson/Potential.html#StandardModel.HiggsField.Potential.isBounded_of_𝓵_pos\"><span class=\"name\">StandardModel</span>.<span class=\"name\">HiggsField</span>.<span class=\"name\">Potential</span>.<span class=\"name\">isBounded_of_𝓵_pos</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">P</span> : <a href=\"./PhysLean/Particles/StandardModel/HiggsBoson/Potential.html#StandardModel.HiggsField.Potential\">Potential</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">h</span> : <span class=\"fn\">0</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LT.lt\">&lt;</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">P</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/Particles/StandardModel/HiggsBoson/Potential.html#StandardModel.HiggsField.Potential.𝓵\">𝓵</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">P</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/Particles/StandardModel/HiggsBoson/Potential.html#StandardModel.HiggsField.Potential.IsBounded\">IsBounded</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Given a element `P` of `Potential` with `0 < 𝓵`, then the potential is bounded. ","docLink":"./PhysLean/Particles/StandardModel/HiggsBoson/Potential.html#StandardModel.HiggsField.Potential.isBounded_of_𝓵_pos","kind":"theorem","line":355,"name":"StandardModel.HiggsField.Potential.isBounded_of_𝓵_pos","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L355-L363"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/Particles/StandardModel/HiggsBoson/Potential.html#StandardModel.HiggsField.Potential.isBounded_𝓵_nonneg\"><span class=\"name\">StandardModel</span>.<span class=\"name\">HiggsField</span>.<span class=\"name\">Potential</span>.<span class=\"name\">isBounded_𝓵_nonneg</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">P</span> : <a href=\"./PhysLean/Particles/StandardModel/HiggsBoson/Potential.html#StandardModel.HiggsField.Potential\">Potential</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">h</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">P</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/Particles/StandardModel/HiggsBoson/Potential.html#StandardModel.HiggsField.Potential.IsBounded\">IsBounded</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\">0</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LE.le\">≤</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">P</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/Particles/StandardModel/HiggsBoson/Potential.html#StandardModel.HiggsField.Potential.𝓵\">𝓵</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Given a element `P` of `Potential` which is bounded,\nthe quartic coefficient `𝓵` of `P` is non-negative. ","docLink":"./PhysLean/Particles/StandardModel/HiggsBoson/Potential.html#StandardModel.HiggsField.Potential.isBounded_𝓵_nonneg","kind":"theorem","line":309,"name":"StandardModel.HiggsField.Potential.isBounded_𝓵_nonneg","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L309-L353"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/Particles/StandardModel/HiggsBoson/Potential.html#StandardModel.HiggsField.Potential.IsBounded\"><span class=\"name\">StandardModel</span>.<span class=\"name\">HiggsField</span>.<span class=\"name\">Potential</span>.<span class=\"name\">IsBounded</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">P</span> : <a href=\"./PhysLean/Particles/StandardModel/HiggsBoson/Potential.html#StandardModel.HiggsField.Potential\">Potential</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Given a element `P` of `Potential`, the proposition `IsBounded P` is true if and only if\nthere exists a real `c` such that for all Higgs fields `φ` and spacetime points `x`,\nthe Higgs potential corresponding to `φ` at `x` is greater then or equal to`c`. I.e.\n\n`∀ Φ x, c ≤ P.toFun Φ x`. ","docLink":"./PhysLean/Particles/StandardModel/HiggsBoson/Potential.html#StandardModel.HiggsField.Potential.IsBounded","kind":"def","line":301,"name":"StandardModel.HiggsField.Potential.IsBounded","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L301-L307"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/Particles/StandardModel/HiggsBoson/Potential.html#StandardModel.HiggsField.Potential.pos_𝓵_sol_exists_iff\"><span class=\"name\">StandardModel</span>.<span class=\"name\">HiggsField</span>.<span class=\"name\">Potential</span>.<span class=\"name\">pos_𝓵_sol_exists_iff</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">P</span> : <a href=\"./PhysLean/Particles/StandardModel/HiggsBoson/Potential.html#StandardModel.HiggsField.Potential\">Potential</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">h𝓵</span> : <span class=\"fn\">0</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LT.lt\">&lt;</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">P</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/Particles/StandardModel/HiggsBoson/Potential.html#StandardModel.HiggsField.Potential.𝓵\">𝓵</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">c</span> : <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\">(∃ (<span class=\"fn\">φ</span> : <a href=\"./PhysLean/Particles/StandardModel/HiggsBoson/Basic.html#StandardModel.HiggsField\">HiggsField</a>) (<span class=\"fn\">x</span> : <a href=\"./PhysLean/SpaceAndTime/SpaceTime/Basic.html#SpaceTime\">SpaceTime</a>), <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">P</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/Particles/StandardModel/HiggsBoson/Potential.html#StandardModel.HiggsField.Potential.toFun\">toFun</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">φ</span> <span class=\"fn\">x</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\">c</span>)</span> <a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Iff\">↔</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">P</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/Particles/StandardModel/HiggsBoson/Potential.html#StandardModel.HiggsField.Potential.μ2\">μ2</a></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LT.lt\">&lt;</a> <span class=\"fn\">0</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#And\">∧</a> <span class=\"fn\">0</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LE.le\">≤</a> <span class=\"fn\">c</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Or\">∨</a> <span class=\"fn\">0</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LE.le\">≤</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">P</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/Particles/StandardModel/HiggsBoson/Potential.html#StandardModel.HiggsField.Potential.μ2\">μ2</a></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#And\">∧</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Neg.neg\">-</a><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">P</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/Particles/StandardModel/HiggsBoson/Potential.html#StandardModel.HiggsField.Potential.μ2\">μ2</a></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HPow.hPow\">^</a> <span class=\"fn\">2</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HDiv.hDiv\">/</a> (<span class=\"fn\">4</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HMul.hMul\">*</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">P</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/Particles/StandardModel/HiggsBoson/Potential.html#StandardModel.HiggsField.Potential.𝓵\">𝓵</a></span>) <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LE.le\">≤</a> <span class=\"fn\">c</span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"For an element `P` of `Potential` with `0 < l` and a real `c : ℝ`, there exists\n  a Higgs field `φ` and a spacetime point `x` such that `P.toFun φ x = c` iff one of the\n  following two conditions hold:\n- `μ2 < 0` and `0 ≤ c`. That is, if `l` is positive and `μ2` negative, then the potential\n  takes every non-negative value.\n- or `0 ≤ μ2` and `- μ2 ^ 2 / (4 * 𝓵) ≤ c`. That is, if `l` is positive and `μ2` non-negative,\n  then the potential takes every value greater then or equal to its bound.\n","docLink":"./PhysLean/Particles/StandardModel/HiggsBoson/Potential.html#StandardModel.HiggsField.Potential.pos_𝓵_sol_exists_iff","kind":"theorem","line":279,"name":"StandardModel.HiggsField.Potential.pos_𝓵_sol_exists_iff","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L279-L293"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/Particles/StandardModel/HiggsBoson/Potential.html#StandardModel.HiggsField.Potential.neg_𝓵_sol_exists_iff\"><span class=\"name\">StandardModel</span>.<span class=\"name\">HiggsField</span>.<span class=\"name\">Potential</span>.<span class=\"name\">neg_𝓵_sol_exists_iff</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">P</span> : <a href=\"./PhysLean/Particles/StandardModel/HiggsBoson/Potential.html#StandardModel.HiggsField.Potential\">Potential</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">h𝓵</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">P</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/Particles/StandardModel/HiggsBoson/Potential.html#StandardModel.HiggsField.Potential.𝓵\">𝓵</a></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LT.lt\">&lt;</a> <span class=\"fn\">0</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">c</span> : <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\">(∃ (<span class=\"fn\">φ</span> : <a href=\"./PhysLean/Particles/StandardModel/HiggsBoson/Basic.html#StandardModel.HiggsField\">HiggsField</a>) (<span class=\"fn\">x</span> : <a href=\"./PhysLean/SpaceAndTime/SpaceTime/Basic.html#SpaceTime\">SpaceTime</a>), <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">P</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/Particles/StandardModel/HiggsBoson/Potential.html#StandardModel.HiggsField.Potential.toFun\">toFun</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">φ</span> <span class=\"fn\">x</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\">c</span>)</span> <a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Iff\">↔</a> <span class=\"fn\">0</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LT.lt\">&lt;</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">P</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/Particles/StandardModel/HiggsBoson/Potential.html#StandardModel.HiggsField.Potential.μ2\">μ2</a></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#And\">∧</a> <span class=\"fn\">c</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LE.le\">≤</a> <span class=\"fn\">0</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Or\">∨</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">P</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/Particles/StandardModel/HiggsBoson/Potential.html#StandardModel.HiggsField.Potential.μ2\">μ2</a></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LE.le\">≤</a> <span class=\"fn\">0</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#And\">∧</a> <span class=\"fn\">c</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LE.le\">≤</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Neg.neg\">-</a><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">P</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/Particles/StandardModel/HiggsBoson/Potential.html#StandardModel.HiggsField.Potential.μ2\">μ2</a></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HPow.hPow\">^</a> <span class=\"fn\">2</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HDiv.hDiv\">/</a> (<span class=\"fn\">4</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HMul.hMul\">*</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">P</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/Particles/StandardModel/HiggsBoson/Potential.html#StandardModel.HiggsField.Potential.𝓵\">𝓵</a></span>)</div></div>","info":{"doc":"For an element `P` of `Potential` with `l < 0` and a real `c : ℝ`, there exists\n  a Higgs field `φ` and a spacetime point `x` such that `P.toFun φ x = c` iff one of the\n  following two conditions hold:\n- `0 < μ2` and `c ≤ 0`. That is, if `l` is negative and `μ2` positive, then the potential\n  takes every non-positive value.\n- or `μ2 ≤ 0` and `c ≤ - μ2 ^ 2 / (4 * 𝓵)`. That is, if `l` is negative and `μ2` non-positive,\n  then the potential takes every value less then or equal to its bound.\n","docLink":"./PhysLean/Particles/StandardModel/HiggsBoson/Potential.html#StandardModel.HiggsField.Potential.neg_𝓵_sol_exists_iff","kind":"theorem","line":217,"name":"StandardModel.HiggsField.Potential.neg_𝓵_sol_exists_iff","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L217-L277"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/Particles/StandardModel/HiggsBoson/Potential.html#StandardModel.HiggsField.Potential.pos_𝓵_toFun_pos\"><span class=\"name\">StandardModel</span>.<span class=\"name\">HiggsField</span>.<span class=\"name\">Potential</span>.<span class=\"name\">pos_𝓵_toFun_pos</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">P</span> : <a href=\"./PhysLean/Particles/StandardModel/HiggsBoson/Potential.html#StandardModel.HiggsField.Potential\">Potential</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">h</span> : <span class=\"fn\">0</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LT.lt\">&lt;</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">P</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/Particles/StandardModel/HiggsBoson/Potential.html#StandardModel.HiggsField.Potential.𝓵\">𝓵</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">φ</span> : <a href=\"./PhysLean/Particles/StandardModel/HiggsBoson/Basic.html#StandardModel.HiggsField\">HiggsField</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">x</span> : <a href=\"./PhysLean/SpaceAndTime/SpaceTime/Basic.html#SpaceTime\">SpaceTime</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">P</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/Particles/StandardModel/HiggsBoson/Potential.html#StandardModel.HiggsField.Potential.μ2\">μ2</a></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LT.lt\">&lt;</a> <span class=\"fn\">0</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#And\">∧</a> <span class=\"fn\">0</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LE.le\">≤</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">P</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/Particles/StandardModel/HiggsBoson/Potential.html#StandardModel.HiggsField.Potential.toFun\">toFun</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">φ</span> <span class=\"fn\">x</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Or\">∨</a> <span class=\"fn\">0</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LE.le\">≤</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">P</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/Particles/StandardModel/HiggsBoson/Potential.html#StandardModel.HiggsField.Potential.μ2\">μ2</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"If `P.𝓵` is bigger then zero, then if `P.μ2` is less than zero, for all space-time points,\nthe potential is positive `0 ≤ P.toFun φ x`. ","docLink":"./PhysLean/Particles/StandardModel/HiggsBoson/Potential.html#StandardModel.HiggsField.Potential.pos_𝓵_toFun_pos","kind":"theorem","line":211,"name":"StandardModel.HiggsField.Potential.pos_𝓵_toFun_pos","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L211-L215"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/Particles/StandardModel/HiggsBoson/Potential.html#StandardModel.HiggsField.Potential.neg_𝓵_toFun_neg\"><span class=\"name\">StandardModel</span>.<span class=\"name\">HiggsField</span>.<span class=\"name\">Potential</span>.<span class=\"name\">neg_𝓵_toFun_neg</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">P</span> : <a href=\"./PhysLean/Particles/StandardModel/HiggsBoson/Potential.html#StandardModel.HiggsField.Potential\">Potential</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">h</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">P</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/Particles/StandardModel/HiggsBoson/Potential.html#StandardModel.HiggsField.Potential.𝓵\">𝓵</a></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LT.lt\">&lt;</a> <span class=\"fn\">0</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">φ</span> : <a href=\"./PhysLean/Particles/StandardModel/HiggsBoson/Basic.html#StandardModel.HiggsField\">HiggsField</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">x</span> : <a href=\"./PhysLean/SpaceAndTime/SpaceTime/Basic.html#SpaceTime\">SpaceTime</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\">0</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LT.lt\">&lt;</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">P</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/Particles/StandardModel/HiggsBoson/Potential.html#StandardModel.HiggsField.Potent